other_tests.findings: The appendix measures 11 mm at its proximal portion with a hyperemic thickened wall and subtle fat stranding around the area. The more distal portion/tip of the appendix appears normal. No adenopathy is present. Normal aortic caliber. Liver, gallbladder, spleen, adrenal glands, pancreas are within normal limits. Right kidney has a tiny sub-cm hypodensity, likely a renal cyst. Fluid is noted in an enlarged endometrial canal.
